---
description: Enforce controller/usecase/repository boundaries in Flutter features
alwaysApply: true
---

# Controller and UseCase Boundaries

- Views/presentation read state providers and trigger actions only through controllers.
- Controllers orchestrate feature actions through use cases only.
- Controllers must not call repositories directly.
- Controllers must not call remote/local data sources directly.
- Repository access is allowed only inside use cases and repository layer flow.
- Keep flow strict: `View -> Controller -> UseCase -> Repository -> DataSource`.

# Practical Enforcement

- If a controller needs a new action (upload/delete/rate/etc.), create/use a dedicated use case.
- Do not bypass use cases for "small" operations.
